Since the Karamanlides did not live only in this geography and other Anatolian Greeks were later called Karamanlides, I changed the article as follows: *The place where the people of Karamanlides are concentrated.
The presence of Christians but Turkish-speaking people in the Bithynia region is also included with the sources.
Manavs are not Kipchak or Oghuz. They are the oldest indigenous people of Anatolia. its origins date back to Hittite, Phrygian, Thracian, Bithynians and Slavs
